org.eclipse.paho.mqttv5.client.alpha

Interface IMqttSubscriptionToken<C>

  • Type Parameters:
    C - The OSGI Promise
    All Superinterfaces:
    IMqttToken<IMqttSubscriptionResult<C>,C>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MqttSubscriptionToken

    public interface IMqttSubscriptionToken<C>
extends IMqttToken<IMqttSubscriptionResult<C>,C>
    Provides a mechanism for tracking a subscription to one or more topics.

    A subclass of IMqttToken that allows a subscription to be tracked. Unlike instances of IMqttToken subscription tokens can be used across connection and client restarts. This enables the receipt of messages to continue after failures.

    A list of subscription tokens for can be obtained using IMqttCommonClient.getSubscribers().

    A subscription request is not made until a terminal operation is invoked on the PushStream returned by getStream(). The result of this request is reflected in the promise returned by IMqttSubscriptionTokenIMqttToken.getPromise().

    • Method Detail

      • getStream

        org.osgi.util.pushstream.PushStream<IReceivedMessage<C>> getStream()
                                                            throws org.eclipse.paho.mqttv5.common.MqttException
        Returns the stream of messages to which this subscription is subscribed.

        Initially this stream is not connected and the subscription request is only sent once a terminal operation is called on the returned stream.

        The subscription is automatically unsubscribed if the stream closes. This may be as a result of negative backpressure from one of the stream pipeline stages, as a result of calling PushStream.close() on the returned stream. If the stream is closed before it is first connected then no subscription request will ever be sent.

        Returns:
        A stream of messages for this subscription
        Throws:
        org.eclipse.paho.mqttv5.common.MqttException - if an exception occurs whilsr returning the stream.

      • getTopics

        List<String> getTopics()
        Returns the topic string(s) for the action being tracked by this token. If the action has not been initiated or the action has not topic associated with it such as connect then null will be returned.
        Returns:
        the topic string(s) for the subscribe being tracked by this token or null
